com.xilinx.rapidwright.design

Class Cell

  • Object
    • com.xilinx.rapidwright.design.Cell
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<Cell>

    public class Cell
extends Object
implements Serializable, Comparable<Cell>
    A cell corresponds to the leaf cell within the logical netlist EDIFCellInst and provides a mapping to a physical location BEL on the device. It could also be called a BELInst.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • isPlacedOn

        public boolean isPlacedOn(SiteTypeEnum type,
                          String bel)
        Compares the placement of the cell with the provided site type and BEL.

        Vivado Tcl:

        if [expr {[get_property BEL $this] eq "$type.$bel}] {1} else {0}

        Parameters:
        type - The type of site to check if this cell is placed on.
        bel - The BEL to check if this cell is placed on.
        Returns:
        True if the site type and BEL match this cell's placement, false otherwise.
        Since:
        2018.2.0

      • fixPin

        public void fixPin(String physicalPin)
        Marks a pin on the cell as fixed by its physical name. A fixed pin cannot be swapped by Vivado.

        Vivado Tcl:

        foreach p [get_pins -of $this] {if [expr {get_bel_pins -of $p eq ""}] {set_property IS_LOC_FIXED 1 $p}

        Parameters:
        physicalPin - Physical name that maps to the logical pin of a cell that is to be fixed.
        Since:
        2018.2.0

      • unFixPin

        public void unFixPin(String physicalPin)
        Unmarks a pin on the cell as fixed by its physical name. Unfixed pins can be swapped by Vivado.

        Vivado Tcl:

        foreach p [get_pins -of $this] {if [expr {get_bel_pins -of $p eq ""}] {set_property IS_LOC_FIXED 0 $p}

        Parameters:
        physicalPin - Physical name that maps to the logical pin of a cell to set as unfixed.
        Since:
        2018.2.0

        public void fixCell(boolean isFixed)

        Parameters:

        Since:
